-- S&P 500 index tops all-time closing high
-- 
-- Mon May 21, 2007 12:14pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/21/us-markets-stocks-sp-idUSN2131901820070521

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The Standard & Poor's 500 index  .SPX  on Monday rose above the record closing high set in March 2000, lifted by the latest news of merger and acquisition activity in telecommunications and health care. 

 The S&P 500 rose intraday to 1,529.25 shortly after noon. The S&P 500's record closing high of 1,527.46 was set on March 24, 2000, in the same month that marked the end of the dot-com stock boom. The S&P 500 also set its all-time high of 1,552.92 on March 24, 2000. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index  .SPX  was last up 6.23 points, or 0.41 percent, at 1,528.98, while the Dow Jones industrial average  .DJI  was up 26.65 points, or 0.19 percent, at 13,583.18 and the Nasdaq Composite Index  .IXIC  was up 29.23 points, or 1.14 percent, at 2,587.68.